Analysis of missing data patterns

Vincent Bagilet, LÃ©o Zabrocki

In this document, we analyse missing data patterns in the dataset. The dataset has been obtained as described in the document âDownload subsample of pollution dataâ (ie using europollution package and downloading data for a random sample of 10% of the stations, from 2013 to 2018). In a first step, we focus on one pollutant only, PM10. The present document is build so that it can be easily modified and recomputed for other pollutants or another sample.

Location of measurement stations

load("../Outputs/metadata.Rda")
load("../Outputs/subsample_stations_ids.Rda")

wrangled_metadata <- metadata %>% 
  ep_wrangle_metadata() 

map_raster <- map_data("world")

wrangled_metadata %>% 
  mutate(
    in_subsample = (station_id %in% subsample_stations_ids)
  ) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_point(aes(x = longitude, y = latitude, color = in_subsample), size = .02) +
  # geom_polygon(data = map_raster, 
  #                        aes(x = long, y = lat, group=group), 
  #                        color = "grey", fill = NA) +
  coord_map(projection = "azequidistant") +
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Dark2") 

wrangled_metadata %>% 
  leaflet() %>%
  addTiles() %>%    # Add OpenStreetMap map tiles
  # setView(lng = 2.34, lat = 48.85, zoom = 5 ) %>% 
  addProviderTiles("Stadia.AlidadeSmooth") %>% 
  addCircles(col =  "orange", lng = ~longitude, lat = ~latitude)
